About the job
Entry-Level Quality Assurance Engineer
Role Description
An Entry-Level Quality Assurance Engineer is responsible for ensuring that software products meet defined quality standards before release. This role involves designing and executing test cases, identifying bugs, and documenting issues in a clear and structured manner. The engineer collaborates with developers and product teams to understand requirements, reproduce defects, and verify fixes. Responsibilities include performing manual and basic automated testing, analyzing system behavior, and contributing to continuous improvement of testing processes. Attention to detail is critical, as the role focuses on detecting inconsistencies, ensuring functionality, and enhancing user experience. The position also requires maintaining test documentation and supporting the development of efficient testing strategies.
Qualifications
A foundational academic background in computer science, software engineering, or a related field is required. Basic knowledge of software testing principles, including functional, regression, and usability testing, is essential. Familiarity with programming or scripting languages, as well as testing tools and frameworks, is advantageous. Strong analytical thinking and problem-solving skills are necessary to identify and troubleshoot issues effectively. The candidate should possess clear communication skills to report findings and collaborate with cross-functional teams. A willingness to learn, adaptability to new technologies, and a detail-oriented mindset are highly valued. The ability to work in a structured and fast-paced environment while maintaining accuracy and consistency is key to success in this role.

