About the job
Why this role might be worth a conversation

You're good at what you do.
You know BMS. You understand HVAC. You've delivered projects before.
But right now… you might feel like you're just repeating the same thing. Same systems. Same clients. Same limitations.

This is different.

You'd be joining a business that's not just delivering BMS projects - it's building a smart buildings platform on AWS that layers AI over everything.
They've already:
Built their own platform analysing energy, air quality, and building performance
Won industry awards for innovation and disruption
Secured major hospital projects with long-term rollout plans

And they're just getting started.
What you'll actually be doing (and why it's interesting)
This isn't a sit-back-and-manage role.
You'll be right in the detail and also driving outcomes.

You'll:
Take ownership of BMS projects from design through to delivery
Work on Tridium Niagara systems across large, complex sites (hospitals, multi-site portfolios)
Coordinate subcontractors, commissioning, and delivery
Work closely with engineering, software and leadership teams
Be client-facing - helping shape solutions, not just deliver them

And here's the key part…
You won't just be delivering projects.

You'll be helping define how they're delivered moving forward - improving processes, influencing strategy, and playing a part in scaling the business globally.

Where you'll be doing it
You'll be joining a Melbourne-based PropTech company (Mulgrave office) that's spent the last few years building something genuinely different.
They're now at the point where things are accelerating:
Scaling their platform globally across AWS
Rolling out major BMS upgrades across healthcare portfolios
Expanding from a small, high-performing team into something much bigger

It's a collaborative, in-office environment - not a clock-in, clock-out culture.
If you like working closely with smart people, having a say, and being part of something early… you'll probably enjoy it here.

If you want a quiet, steady, low-change environment… this won't be for you.
What you'll need

You don't need to tick every box, but you'll likely have:
Strong experience with BMS systems (Tridium Niagara essential)
Solid understanding of HVAC systems and building services
Experience delivering projects (or stepping into project management)
Ability to handle multiple projects and stakeholders
Good communication - you're comfortable speaking with clients
A hands-on mindset (you're not above getting into the detail when needed)

What's in it for you
$130k - $170k + Super (depending on experience)
Staff share scheme - tied to company and individual performance
Real progression as the business scales (locally and globally)
Exposure to cutting-edge smart building + AI technology
A role where you can actually influence outcomes, not just follow process

And importantly…
You'll be joining at the stage where things are about to take off - not after it's already happened.
What next
If this sounds like something you'd want to explore:
You don't need a perfect CV.
Just send what you have or reach out for a chat.
We can talk through the role, the projects, and whether it makes sense for you.

