About the job
Work options: Hybrid

KJR is looking for a Performance & Load Test Specialist who will be responsible for planning, designing, executing, and reporting on performance, load, stress, and scalability testing across a complex portfolio of applications in preparation for a major event. The role will ensure that both public\u2011facing and internal systems can safely handle expected and peak workloads, including extreme concurrency, high transaction volumes, and time\u2011critical processing windows.

This role requires someone who can operate with incomplete or evolving non\u2011functional requirements, work closely with business stakeholders, DevOps, and development teams, and define realistic performance test scenarios based on real operational usage.

Start Date: As soon as possible

Duration: 3 months (with possible extension)

Key Responsibilities

Performance Test Planning & Strategy

Own the development and delivery of the performance testing strategy.
Review application scope and determine which systems require performance testing, including advising where testing may be unnecessary or can be deprioritised.
Translate business volumes (e.g. users, transactions per hour, batch sizes) into clear and testable NFRs.
Define performance test entry/exit criteria, success metrics, and risk thresholds.

Performance Test Design & Execution

Design and execute performance tests across:
Public\u2011facing web applications
Internal system applications
Batch and high\u2011volume processing
Create realistic workload models, including:
High concurrency (up to 10,000+ users)
Peak hourly volumes
Long\u2011running batch processes (e.g. millions of records)
Execute:
Load testing
Stress testing
Endurance/soak testing
Scalability testing
Validate system behaviour under peak period conditions.

Tooling & Environment Management

Select and use appropriate performance testing tools (ideally Jmeter since that’s what we have used before).
Work with DevOps to:
Configure test environments
Implement monitoring and logging
Validate horizontal scaling and infrastructure limits
Ensure test environments are representative of production where possible.

Analysis, Reporting & Defect Management

Analyse performance test results to identify:
Application bottlenecks
Infrastructure constraints
Database and integration issues
Produce clear, executive\u2011ready performance reports showing:
Achieved vs expected performance
Risks and recommendations
Go/No\u2011Go readiness assessments
Log, track and retest performance defects through to resolution.

Stakeholder Collaboration

Work closely with:
Quality Assurance
Development teams
DevOps
Business SMEs
Challenge assumptions and provide evidence\u2011based advice on system readiness.
Support decision\u2011making for readiness and operational risk.

Who are we?

Started in a garage on the Gold Coast in 1997, KJR is now a leading Software Quality Engineering consultancy with offices in Melbourne, Brisbane, and Canberra. We specialise in software assurance, AI adoption, and technology risk management, helping organisations unlock real value from emerging technologies.

At the forefront of Trusted AI Adoption, we ensure AI solutions are ethical, compliant, and drive meaningful business outcomes.

Our people—The Collective—are central to our success. We support your growth through career development, recognition programs and our annual team conference.

KJR is proud to be Certified by Great Place To Work® and to foster a diverse and inclusive culture, recognised by the 2023 AIIA Diversity Award.

We’re driven to make a difference—and you can help make it happen.

Learn more: www.kjr.com.au

Explore our innovation projects: https://kjr.com.au/corporate-social-responsibility/

Interested? Select “Apply”, create a profile in our Talent Community, and we’ll be in touch.

